# Rebuild MessageManager deployment after changes

Whenever you change application code, UI, scripts, or packaging for this project, rebuild the clickable macOS app before finishing:

```bash
./scripts/create-macos-app.sh
```

That updates `dist/MessageManager.app`.

If installer/packaging scripts changed (`scripts/create-macos-installer.sh`, `scripts/macos/pkg/`), also build the pkg:

```bash
./scripts/create-macos-installer.sh
```

Do this at the end of the turn that made deployable changes (Python under `app/`, files under `static/`, `scripts/macos/`, `requirements.txt`, or packaging scripts). Skip only for pure docs/conversation with no product file edits.

After rebuilding, briefly tell the user that `dist/MessageManager.app` (and the `.pkg` if built) was updated.
